## Permitted Tools

### Google Calendar (GoG CLI) — LIVE AFTER SETUP
GoG CLI installed at `/usr/local/bin/gog`. OAuth authorization required for each account.

**Authorized Accounts:**
| Account | Purpose | Access |
|---------|---------|--------|
| `andrew@wastenaut.ai` | Work calendar (full content — Miles is the work agent) | read/write |
| `drew.joiner@gmail.com` | Family calendar (opaque — time blocks only) | read-only |

**Quick Reference Commands:**
```bash
# List work events this week (default account = andrew@wastenaut.ai)
gog calendar list --from 2026-03-17 --to 2026-03-23 --plain

# List family calendar as opaque blocks (strip content before processing)
gog calendar list --account drew.joiner@gmail.com --from 2026-03-17 --to 2026-03-23 --plain

# Create a work calendar event
gog calendar create --summary "Focus: Stream API" --start "2026-03-17T09:00:00" --end "2026-03-17T11:00:00"
```

**Privacy Rules:**
- **Family calendar (drew.joiner@gmail.com):** NEVER show event titles, descriptions, or attendees. Only report time blocks as "Personal Conflict [start-end]".
- **Work calendar (andrew@wastenaut.ai):** Full content access. This is Miles's primary domain.

### Apollo API — Read-Only
```bash
# Example: Get active opportunities
curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $APOLLO_API_KEY" \
  "https://api.apollo.io/v1/opportunities?status=active"
```
- Contact records, deal stages, enrichment data
- Pipeline state for observation and memory writes
- V1: read-only. No writes to Apollo.

### Todoist API — Read-Only
```bash
# Example: Get all active tasks
curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TODOIST_API_TOKEN" \
  "https://api.todoist.com/rest/v2/tasks"
```
- Task list with deadlines, priorities, project assignments
- Completion history via activity log
- V1: read-only. No writes to Todoist.

### Work Vault — Read-Only (V1)
- Path: `/home/openclaw/work-vault/`
- Git-synced every 10 minutes via systemd timer
- Read all files freely — this is Miles's primary knowledge base
- V1: No writes to vault. V2+: write to `Miles Outputs/` only.
- Key paths:
  - `0. Dashboard/Daily Snapshots/` — Cowork daily-scan output
  - `0. Dashboard/Weekly/` — Weekly planning docs
  - `1. Projects/` — Project notes with status, tasks, blockers
  - `2. Areas/` — Strategy, products, positioning, data capabilities

### Telegram — Send/Receive
- Primary communication channel with Andrew
- V1: Respond only when Andrew messages directly. No unsolicited messages.
- Message format: plain text, scannable, no markdown unless helpful

### File Read/Write — Workspace Only
- Read: workspace/ (all agent config, memory, logs, skills)
- Write: workspace/MEMORY.md, workspace/logs/, workspace/daily/
